Fill Generation and Insertion

** This file is for the Oasis flow (all input, output files in Oasis format) **
** The steps for the GDS flow are similar **
** Note that the fill cell GDS is called:  poly_diff_FILLCELL.gds.gz **

** Oasis flow is recommended as the file sizes will be smaller **

OVERVIEW:

This directory contains a "beta" fill generation routine and control scripts.

Flow:
[1]   Export oasis file of top level design from Virtuoso
[2]   Run fill generation routine; creates separate Oasis file
[3a]  Insert poly-diff fill cell into fill file from [2]; creates new Oasis file
[3b]  Insert fill file from [3a] into top level design; creates new Oasis file
[4]   Import design Oasis file with fill from [3b] into Virtuoso
[5]   Run SKY130 DRC

** A poly-diff fill cell is used since poly fill and diff fill cannot overlap. **

Steps 3a & 3b require the use of Pegasus Design Review. 
User can instead import the Oasis files into their layout tool for insertion.

USAGE:

[1]  ENV Variables

User should have the following ENV variables set appropriately:

  setenv PDK_HOME    /projects/SkyWater/sky130_release_0.0.9
  setenv PEGASUS_DRC /projects/SkyWater/Sky130_DRC_rev_0.0_2.8

[2]  Libraries

cds.lib must be updated to point to user's design libraries.

[3]  Poly & diff fill cell

The fill cell oasis file must be present in this directory:

	poly_diff_FILLCELL.oasis
	
[4}  Fill generation Pegasus routine

The file "fillgen.pvl" must be copied to this directory

[5]  Executable Files 

  step1_oasisout.csh	- makes top level design Oasis file: CELLNAME.oasis
  step2_fillgen.csh	- makes fill Oasis file: 	     CELLNAME.fill.oasis
  step3_merge.csh	- merges fill cell & fill data into top level:
  	3a: Inserts poly_diff_FILLCELL into fill, outputs:   CELLNAME.fill_aref.oas
	3b: Inserts fill data into top level, outputs:	     CELLNAME.wFill.oas	
  step4_oasisin.csh	- makes Virtuoso library (user controlled library name)
  step5_sky130_DRC.csh 	- runs sky130 DRC on resulting filled data

[6]  Control Files 

  step 2:  fill_CTL.pvl
  step 3a: pdr_CTL_aref
  step 3b: pdr_CTL
  step 5:  drc_CTL.pvl

[7]  Edits

** In all executable and control files, the following changes must be made: **

  MYLIBRARY ->  user's Virtuoso library containing layout to fill
  CELLNAME  ->  user's top level layout cell name to fill

In "step1_oasisout.csh" 
	"-libary" option must be updated
	"-layerMap" option must be updated
	
In "step4_oasisin.csh" 
	"-library" option can be changed as desired
	"-layerMap" option must be updated

In "step5_run_sky130_DRC.csh" the "-run_dir" option can be changed as desired.

[8] Outputs

CELLNAME.oas		- top level Oasis file, created by step 1
CELLNAME.fill.oas	- fill (only) Oasis file, created by step 2
CELLNAME.fill_aref.oas	- fill (only) file, with poly-fill cell inserted
CELLNAME.wFill.oas	- top level Oasis file, with fill inserted !!

step 4 will create the Virtuoso library locally
step 5 will create the DRC run directory locally

